04/04/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US government has condemned a recent spate of bombings carried out by the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) in Turkey.
Deputy State Department spokesman Adam Ereli also expressed regret Monday (3 April) for the loss of life in violent protests by PKK supporters.
He referred to Turkey as "an ally and a close friend" and urged restraint by all parties.
(US State Department press release - 04/04/06;
AP - 03/04/06)
